Good — at a ₹7,000 premium with Zero‑Dep + RTI for your 2018 Swift VXi you get comprehensive own‑damage + third‑party cover plus these key items:  
1) IDV: final insured declared value set after inspection (typical for a 2018 Swift VXi ~₹1.8–2.5 lakh, I’ll confirm exact IDV);  
2) Zero‑Dep: waiver of depreciation on plastic/metal/engine parts for approved OD claims (subject to insurer age/claim limits);  
3) RTI: pays the invoice shortfall over IDV on total loss/theft;  
4) Towing/Roadside & consumables: emergency towing/assistance and limited consumables (nuts/bolts/oil) up to insurer limits (commonly ~₹1,500–3,000/incident);  
5) Engine/electrical: covers accidental damage from insured perils but NOT mechanical wear‑and‑tear or breakdowns;  
6) NCB protection: protects your no‑claim bonus per insurer terms (usually covers one claim).  

Claims are settled cashless at network garages or by reimbursement after inspection; payouts are subject to IDV, policy exclusions and your ₹20,000 voluntary deductible (so settlement = admissible loss − ₹20,000). I can pull the live insurer schedule now to lock exact limits and exclusions for this ₹7,000 option.
